Peru Stocks: Cementos Lima, Edegel, Ferreyros, Siderperu, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-22T21:21:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/peru-stocks-cementos-lima-edegel-ferreyros-siderperu-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index gained 2.7 percent to 21,961.66. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.6 percent to 2,948.23.  Construction and utilities stocks gained after investors
who sold their shares in  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI) ’s Peruvian subsidiary
bought other stocks, said Miguel Pancorvo, head trader at Lima-
based brokerage Compass SAB.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, jumped 7 percent to 38 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
rose 5.6 percent to 3.97 soles.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1) 
(TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of Telefonica SA, rose 5.5 percent
to 3.43 soles after the company said it plans to sell $18
million of seven-year debt.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1) 
(SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest
steelmaker, gained 5.1 percent to 1.65 soles. Edegel SA
(EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s Endesa SA, rose 4.4
percent to 1.88 soles.  Copper, zinc and tin miners rose after metals advanced in
New York and  London .  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, surged 8.8 percent to 4.57 soles. Cia. Minera Atacocha
SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc producer, rose
5.8 percent to 1.28 soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA
(CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc.,
rose 4.8 percent to $46.50.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a
Canadian exploration company, rose 4.5 percent to $1.87 after it
said it resumed drilling at its Canariaco deposit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
